		<div class="block-contributor-content">
		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><strong><span class="smallcaps">Alan Craig</span></strong> is the pseudonym of an aging writer with funny hair. Years ago he experienced chest pains while waiting at a ticket counter in a train station. Certain it was a heart attack and too embarrassed to ask a stranger for help, he bought his ticket and staggered to the train, hoping for the best. He wonders if this means that he&rsquo;d rather drop dead than make a scene.</p><a href="/contributors/alan-craig" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
